# Build standards (`build`)

Invoke this rule before implementing features. Prefer clarity over cleverness.

## Core

- **KISS** — simplest solution that meets the request; no premature abstraction
- **DRY** — extract a helper only when the same logic is real and repeated (not speculative)
- **Readable** — a human should understand the code without a tour; boring linear code beats clever indirection
- **Comment why**, not what; skip obvious narration
- **Do not hallucinate** — check the repo for APIs, columns, env vars, helpers before inventing them
- **Scope** — only change what the request needs; no drive-by refactors or unrelated files

## This repo

- Fixed rental roles + `can()` from `@/lib/auth/rental-permissions` — no DIY permission matrices
- UK dates/times via `@/lib/datetime/uk` helpers — not raw ISO or browser locale
- Theme: `rph-*` tokens / utilities from `globals.css` — no ad-hoc `dark:bg-zinc-*` stacks on new UI
- DB changes: migration + idempotent `supabase/manual/ensure_*.sql` when schema changes
- Match nearby patterns (server actions, FormModalShell, overlays, vehicle workspace)

## Multi-step modals (UI consistency)

Use the same chrome for every stepped `FormModalShell` flow:

- **Shell** — `FormModalShell` from `@/components/forms/form-modal-shell` (backdrop does not dismiss; Close/Cancel + discard confirm)
- **Progress** — `FormModalStepProgress` in `headerExtra` with a `STEP_LABELS` array; **0-based** `step` prop (`step - 1` if your wizard stores 1-based steps)
- **Title** — stable action name (`New hire contract`, `Add vehicle`); put “Step X of Y” in the progress component, not the title
- **Footer** — `Cancel` left; `Back` / primary action right via `formModalBtnGhost` / `formModalBtnContinue` from `@/components/forms/form-modal-actions`
- **Fields** — `rph-input`, `FormModalField`, `rph-meta`, `rph-card`; UK dates via `@/lib/datetime/uk`
- **Drafts** — browser drafts: `useFormModalDraft` + shell `onSaveProgress` / `onSaveAndClose`; server drafts: `showDraftActions={false}` and a footer `formModalBtnSecondary` “Save draft” that calls your server action
- **Large forms** — `allowMaximize` + `maxWidthClass` when needed (match hire/terms modals)
- **Reference** — `add-vehicle-modal.tsx`, `register-subcompany-modal.tsx`, `hire-contract-wizard-modal.tsx`

Do not invent a new step indicator or footer button layout when extending an existing wizard.

## Product safety

- Do not silently invent or restore history (e.g. previous MOT expiry) without stored data
- Keep expense logs separate from vehicle source-of-truth fields unless the feature explicitly updates both
- Permissions and RLS must stay aligned with fixed roles

## Validate (unit tests)

Vitest lives in `apps/web` (`*.test.ts` next to the module under `src/`).

**Goal:** every **pure** exported function in `src/lib` has unit tests (happy path + branches).

- Pure = sync logic with no Supabase/Next/fetch/env secrets (dates, money, permissions, identity, validation, mapping, etc.)
- **Not** unit-tested here: server actions, React pages, Supabase queries, PDF/mail, env-keyed crypto — validate those manually or with later integration tests
- When you add a new pure helper, add `foo.test.ts` beside it covering all exports and branches
- **After each implementation:** `npm test` (root) or `npm run test --workspace=@rph/web`
- **To verify coverage of the pure set:** `npm run test:coverage --workspace=@rph/web` (see `vitest.config.ts` `PURE_LIB_COVERAGE`)
- Still include a short manual check list for UI wiring
- **Do not** invent flaky E2E unless the user asks

Colocate tests as `foo.test.ts` beside `foo.ts`. Keep tests deterministic (`vi.useFakeTimers()` for “today”).
